Head of Service of the Federation (HoSF), Dr. Folasade Yemi-Esan, has urged the leadership of the National Assembly to revise its Consolidated Salary Structure (CONLESS). She contended that the process leading to the new pay for civil servants in the National Assembly was faulty and illegal. Yemi-Esan, during a meeting with Senate President Ahmad Lawan and Speaker Femi Gbajabiamila of the House of Representatives in Abuja, faulted the emolument review by the eighth Assembly. She argued that the establishment was not different from the core civil service to warrant a dedicated salary regime. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .